<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Girlge on 09-22-2000 04:53 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I don't think he'd be Omat Vastsea would be on Beta Neutral faction if he was not meant for all races of Clerics.

The Plasmatic Priesthood guy glowers at my DE Cleric as well.

Those two things lead me to believe it is the same for all Clerics, that the Triumvirate are the "good guys" and the Plasmatic Priesthood are the "bad guys." After all, Innoruuk, Bertox, Cazic Thule have no ties with Fennin Ro, nor to the good dieties necessarily have any ties with E'ci, Tarew Marr, or Povar.

Right now, it seems like our best lead is to track down this Bergurgle fellow and see if we can't kill him. He could reside in any water-zone. I've checked Dagnor's and Lake Rathe. Found nothing in Dagnor's, found only old Webclaw and a new NPC "Deep". Deep is pretty tough, just killed her today (doesn't respond to any hails), seemed to have 32K HPs, hit for 170, and procs an Ice based Tepid Deeds + Snare. She dropped ... "Red Wine." Seems to be just ordinary red whine that you can purchase at any bar. She may be someone you seek out and give an item or note to from another quest, or maybe later on in our own.

At any rate, has anyone checked TD or OOT for Bergurgle?</TEXTAREA>
